The paper deals with the construction of algebraic geometric codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the study of Weierstrass semigroups and pure gaps, which are concepts in computational complexity (cs.CC) and cryptography (cs.CR). The determination of the floor of a certain type of divisor is related to number theory and algebraic geometry, which are topics in data structures (cs.DS) and scientific computing (cs.SI).
